<H2>Alcohol Policy</h2>

<H2>The Ultimate Employee Handbook -- A Workshop</h2>

<H3>Workshop Discussion Thread</h3>


From: Carolyn Gorwitz -- Royal Crown Co. - Fort Lauderdale<br>
Date: Thu Jan 18 13:10:20 1996<br>
Subject: Alcohol policy<p>

Does anyone include a policy re: alcohol use during lunch...while
it may be a good policy from a preventative measure, it seems to
smack of big brother and may be unreasonable in an environment
where deals may be discussed with overseas visitors who think it
perfectly natural to have a glass of wine or speck of beer over
mid day discussions. Perhaps a policy that one should not drive
if their judgment is in any way impaired by the use of alcohol
and should not be drinking to a point where it will effect their
ability to do their job.<p>

