15 In the U.S., PGP ViaCrypt 2.7 is a 128-bit product which is licensed for
commercial use in the U.S. Outside the U.S., it is a simple matter to download
PGP 2.6ui ("unofficial international", whose code was written entirely outside
the U.S.) from a number of Internet sites which are outside the U.S. PGP 2.6ui
is a 128-bit product which is interoperable with PGP ViaCrypt 2.7. PGP 2.6ui
allegedly would infringe U.S. patents if it were used in the U.S., but there are
no corresponding patents outside the U.S. The net result is that a U.S.
corporation or attorney can achieve global (except in certain countries which
prohibit the use of strong encryption) secure 128-bit security services today by
using PGP ViaCrypt 2.7 in the U.S., and by asking its correspondents outside the
U.S. to obtain and use PGP ViaCrypt 2.6ui outside the U.S.<p> 


16 "Quite simply, the hopelessly polarized warfare over the privacy issues of
