<H4>Editor's Note: Here is a sample of a disclaimer for use with Employee
Handbooks.</h4>

* * *

<H3>Employee Handbook Disclaimer</h3>

The contents of this handbook summarize current company programs and
policies and are intended as guidelines only. They may be amended by the
company at any time.<p>

THE CONTENTS OF THIS HANDBOOK DO NOT CONSTITUTE THE TERMS OF A CONTRACT
OF EMPLOYMENT AND SHOULD NOT BE CONSTRUED AS A GUARANTEE OF CONTINUED
EMPLOYMENT WITH THE COMPANY. EMPLOYMENT WITH THE COMPANY IS ON AN 
<A HREF="http://www.courttv.com/legalhelp/business/workplace/660.html">
AT WILL</a> BASIS. This means that the employment relationship may be
terminated at any time by either the company or the employee for any
reason not expressly prohibited by law. Any oral or written statement by
anyone, (except those in writing and signed by the director fo human
resources) to the contrary is invalid and should not be relied upon by
any prospective or existing employee.<p></BLOCKQUOTE><P ALIGN=CENTER><br><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/stroke.gif"><BR><A HREF="/map/bottom.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/bottom.gif" ISMAP ALIGN=ABSBOTTOM BORDER=0></A><BR><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/rights.gif" ALT="All Materials Copyright CourtTV 1995. All Rights Reserved. Disclaimer: Nothing in this site is intended to constitute legal advice"></P></BODY></HTML>
