<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H2>Model Employee Handbook Outline</h2>



<H2>The Ultimate Employee Handbook -- A Workshop</h2>



<H3>Workshop Library File</h3>



Contributor: Gerard Morales<br>

Firm: Snell & Wilmer<br>

Address: One Arizona Center, Phoenix, Arizona 85004-0001<br>

Telephone: (602) 382-6362<br>

Fax: (602) 382-6070<p>



E-mail:<A HREF="mailto:jmorales@counsel.com">jmorales@counsel.com</a><p>



<H3>Model Employee Handbook Outline*</h3>

Copyright 1995 by Gerard Morales<p>



Note: Items listed with (e) should be considered essential<p>



I. Introductory<p>



A.  Welcome to Organization<p>



(e) B.  Scope of Handbook (what it is)<p>



(e) C.  Conspicuous Disclaimer (what it is not)<p>



employment at will<p>



explanation of probation (if any)<p>



(e)  D. Code of Ethics<p>



commitment to compliance with statutory requirements<p>



(not intended to extend statute of limitations)<p>



expectation of employees (monitoring and reporting)<p>



prohibition of retaliation<p>



E. Definition of Terms<p>



II. Policies and Procedures<p>



(e)  A. Discipline<p>



compliance as minimum requirement: not equal to adequate<p>



performance<p>



compliance does not affect at-will relationship<p>



possible sanctions: termination, demotion, transfer, suspension,

reprimand, counseling, etc. (not progressive: depends solely on

employer's view of what is appropriate)<p> 



(e)  B.  Prohibition of Harassment<p>



C. General Conduct and Attire<p>



attendance and promptness<p>



attention to duties<p>



compliance with policies and procedures<p>



compliance with supervisory authority<p>



dress code<p>



illegal or unethical conduct<p>



courtesy<p>



gossip and rumors<p>



care of property; avoidance of waste<p>



responsibility for visitors<p>



teamwork<p>



conflict with coworkers<p>



D.  Employment of Family Members<p>



(e) E.  Conflicts of Interest<p>



self-dealing<p>



transactions with family and friends<p>



F.  Confidential Information<p>



requests for employment information<p> 



client lists, confidential processes, etc.<p>



employee files: personnel and medical<p>



G.  Outside Employment<p>



H.  Reimbursement of Expenses<p>



use of personal vehicles<p><UL>



<LI>insurance coverage required<p>



<LI>certification of insurance by agent</ul><p>



(e) I.  Solicitation and Distribution<p>



J.  Substance Abuse<p>



K.  Smoke-Free Environment<p>



L.  Workplace Safety<p>



M.  Open Door Policy<p>



(e) N.  Reporting of Unusual Circumstances<p>



suspected violations of law<p>



serious misconduct<p>



traffic accidents<p>



workplace hazards<p>



(e) O.  Resolution of Disputes<p>



(refer to separate ADR policy)<p>



P.  Procedures for Termination of Employment<p>



by employee<p>



by employer<p>



III.  Employee Benefits<p>



A.  Wages and Salary<p>



FLSA description<p>



time-keeping<p>



requirements for overtime authorization<p>



B.  Time Away from Work<p>



holidays<p>



personal leave<p><UL>



<LI>paid vacation<p>



<LI>jury duty<p>



<LI>military leave<p>



<LI>educational leave<p>



<LI>unpaid personal leave</ul><p>



illness leave<p><UL>



<LI>paid sick leave<p>



<LI>paid disability leave<p>



<LI>workers' compensation (describe law)<p>



<LI>extended medical leave (FMLA description)<p>



<LI>bereavement leave</ul><p>



C. Welfare Plans (for information regarding any of the following

types of plans that may be offered, employees should be referred

to the most recent of the official plan summaries distributed

from time to time)<p>



pension<p>



deferred compensation or other savings incentive<p>



stock purchase<p>



severance payments<p>



medical insurance<p>



life insurance<p>



IV.  Employee Relations Programs<p>



A.  Credit Union<p>



B.  Educational Assistance<p>



C.  Employee Discounts<p>



D.  Service Awards<p>



E.  Company-Sponsored Activities<p>



V.  Separate Employee Waivers and Agreements<p>



A.  Alternative Dispute Resolution<p>



B.  Employee Consent to Drug Testing<p>



new applicants<p>



present employees<p>



