<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H2>Smoking Policy - American Lawyer Media, L.P. </h2>

<H2>The Ultimate Employee Handbook -- A Workshop</h2>

<H3>Workshop Library File</h3>

<H4>Contributor: Cloyd Laporte III<br>

Source: Counsel Connect<br>
Address: 600 Third Ave., 2nd Floor, New York, NY  10016<br>
Telephone: (800) 455-4354<br>
Fax: (212) 692-7855<br>

<A
HREF="mailto:claporte@counsel.com">E-mail:claporte@counsel.com</a></h4><p>

<H3>Smoking Policy</h3>

To:  All Employees Who Smoke<p>

Re:  Smoking During Working Hours<p>

We need your cooperation in a delicate matter: Restricting
the
amount you smoke while youre at work.<p>

None of your supervisors wants to get into the business of
closely regulating your time at work. We want to retain an
informal management style, and we dont want to impose
formal
break times, except in the strictest production settings.
But
its clear that smoking is getting out of hand, and people
are
spending ridiculous amounts of time standing around out-side
sucking nicotine. Somebody who has a half-dozen cigarettes
during
work very likely spends close to an hour a day -- or more --
hanging out.<p>

Let me be clear: We dont want you to smoke at all. It will
make
you sick. It will bring pain to the people who care most
about
you. It also drives up the cost of health insurance benefits
for
the rest of us. (Let me remind you well happily reimburse
the
tuition paid by any smoker who completes a smoke-ending
program
and remains smoke-free for a year.)<p>

We sure dont want to encourage smoking by granting smokers
paid
time off that non-smokers dont get.<p>

So were asking you to confine your smoking to what were
told is
a standard: A break in the morning and a break in the
afternoon.
Please arrange the timing of those breaks with your
supervisor.
Were leaving this up to you, for now.<p>

One more thing: This is a smoke-free environment. You may
not
smoke anywhere in this building at any time. Thats no joke.
We
have many things in our buildings, chemicals and paper for
starters, that burn very well. Smoking in this building is
grounds for immediate dismissal.<p>





</BLOCKQUOTE>
