<H2>Online Legal Updates</H2>

<P>Online Legal Updates are provided by sponsoring lawyers and law firms as a quick, easy way for you to learn more about laws that affect you or your family. Written by individual lawyers or attorneys at law firms from around the country, the Family Law Online Legal Updates are organized by state or jurisdiction because domestic laws vary from state to state, sometimes dramatically. The Updates may include links to legal documents and case law as well as information about the authoring attorney or law firm.</P>

<P>We encourage you to send the authors questions via the e-mail response forms at the end of each Update. Remember, however, that any answers you receive, like the Online Legal Updates themselves, are not legal advice. (See the disclaimer below).</P>

<P>The attorneys and law firms appearing here have paid a sponsorship fee to be listed. If you would like information about including your law firm in the Court TV Family Law Center's Online Legal Update program, or if you have questions or comments about this area, please e-mail your requests and comments to: <A HREF="mailto:online@counsel.com">online@counsel.com</A>.</P>

