<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles: Menendez</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/top-casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/top-casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>The Menendez Retrial: March 1996</H2>

<P>NOTE: These files are in a compressed format (zipped). You will need to <A HREF="/download/utility/">download an unzipping utility</A> to open them.</P>

<P>If you prefer, you may <A HREF="march.zip">download the entire month's transcripts</A> at once.</P>
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<H3>The Transcripts</H3>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: March 29</B> [<I><A HREF="mar29.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The defense called three teachers who knew the Menendez brothers as high school students and Alan Andersen, the brothers' cousin.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: March 28</B> [<I><A HREF="mar28.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The defense began calling many of the witnesses who testified at the first trial about the psychological abuse of Lyle and Erik Menendez at the hands of their parents. The prosecution successfully argued in the second trial that these witnesses were irrelevant to the murders of Kitty and Jose Menendez. But in the penalty phase, Judge Stanley Weisberg has permitted such testimony.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: March 27</B> [<I><A HREF="mar27.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The same jury that found Erik and Lyle Menendez guilty of first-degree murder begins to consider whether the brothers deserve the death penalty.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: March 22</B> [<I><A HREF="mar22.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Judge Stanley Weisberg grants the defense a delay in the start of the penalty phase of the trial to bring out-of-town witnesses to court.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: March 20</B> [<I><A HREF="mar20.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The jury finds the brothers guilty of first-degree murder.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: March 15</B> [<I><A HREF="mar15.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Judge Stanley Weisberg clarifies his instruction that deliberations begin anew, adding that any materials prepared by the original 12 jurors must also be discarded.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: March 14</B> [<I><A HREF="mar14.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Judge Stanley Weisberg replaces two members of the jury who were sick. He instructed the remaining jurors to disregard any deliberations that had already taken place and to start over with the two alternates that replaced the excused jurors.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: March 6</B> [<I><A HREF="mar06.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The jury requested a readback of certain portions of the testimony. The readback was conducted in open court.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: March 1</B> [<I><A HREF="mar01.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The jury received instructions from Judge Stanley Weisberg and began deliberating.</P>

<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/rights2.gif" ALT="Copyright 1996 by American Lawyer Media, L.P. All Rights Reserved.">
