HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Server: Netscape-Communications/1.1
Date: Wednesday, 08-Jan-97 08:24:13 GMT
Last-modified: Wednesday, 24-Jul-96 16:27:37 GMT
Content-length: 6720
Content-type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles: Menendez</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/top-casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/top-casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>The Menendez Retrial: November 1995</H2>

<P>NOTE: These files are in a compressed format (zipped). You will need to <A HREF="/download/utility/">download an unzipping utility</A> to open them.</P>

<P>If you prefer, you may <A HREF="november.zip">download the entire month's transcripts</A> at once.</P>
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<H3>The Transcripts</H3>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 30</B> [<I><A HREF="nov30.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
A criminalist testified that engineer Roger McCarthy, who reconstructed the crime scene for the prosecution, reached many conclusions by ignoring much of the evidence.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 29</B> [<I><A HREF="nov29.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Testifying for the defense, Ron Linhart, the head of the Los Angeles Sheriff's Department crime lab, attacked the prosecution's computer-animated reconstruction of the crime scene.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 28</B> [<I><A HREF="nov28.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
With one juror too sick to come to court, Judge Stanley Weisberg heard arguments over exhibts for about an hour and recessed the court for the day.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 27</B> [<I><A HREF="nov27.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
After an hour of testimony, a juror raised her hand and complained that she was sick. Judge Stanley Weisberg sent the jurors home. He kept the lawyers to argue over exhibits.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 22</B> [<I><A HREF="nov22.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Prosecutor David Conn cross-examined Dr. Martin Fackler, a ballistics expert.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 21</B> [<I><A HREF="nov21.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
A ballistics expert testified for the defense that the conclusions of an engineer who re-created the crime scene for the prosecution were "contrary to fact and frankly nonsense."</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 20</B> [<I><A HREF="nov20.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Having presented 30 witnesses and some 300 exhibits over 27 days, the prosecution rested its case.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 17</B> [<I><A HREF="nov17.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
After several days of cross-examination, witness Roger McCarthy reiterated his belief that Jose and Kitty Menendez were sitting down when they were ambushed by their sons.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 16</B> [<I><A HREF="nov16.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Defense lawyer Leslie Abramson accused crime scene reconstruction expert Roger McCarthy of testifying for the prosecution as a favor to Los Angeles District Attorney Gil Garcetti, "who is on a losing streak."</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 15</B> [<I><A HREF="nov15.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The cross-examination of prosecution witness Roger McCarthy continued.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 14</B> [<I><A HREF="nov14.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The defense tried to show that Roger McCarthy was not qualified to testify about crime scenes. Under questioning by defense attorney Charles Gessler, McCarthy conceded that he has never visited a crime scene or witnessed an autopsy. He also admitted that he has never seen gunshot wounds on an actual body and did not consult with the medical examiner or criminalists before reaching his conclusions about the Menendez case.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 13</B> [<I><A HREF="nov13.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Even though the prosecution hadn't rested its case, Judge Stanley Weisberg ordered the defense to begin calling witnesses. The prosecution's final witness, Roger McCarthy, was unable to testify due to a prior commitment.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 9</B> [<I><A HREF="nov09.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Prosecutors presented computer-generated illustrations of the killngs in an effort to show that the Menendez brothers ambushed their parents.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 8</B> [<I><A HREF="nov08.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Dr. Roger McCarthy, a crime scene reconstruction expert, used high-tech illustrations and bloody autopsy photos in an attempt to show that the Menendez brothers caught their parents by surprise on the night of the shooting.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 7</B> [<I><A HREF="nov07.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Defense attorney Leslie Abramson showed to jurors a blood-caked, short-sleeved shirt worn by Jose Menendez when he was killed. She suggested to pathologist Dr. Robert Lawrence, who testified for the prosecution, that blood patterns on the shirt indicate that the shots might not have been fired in the direction that the prosecution claims.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 6</B> [<I><A HREF="nov06.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The jury was shown dozens of gruesome autopsy photos of Jose and Kitty Menendez as prosecutors began the final phase of their case.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 3</B> [<I><A HREF="nov03.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Jose Menendez's secretary testified about Lyle Menendez's behavior after the murders. She said Menendez wore his father's shoes to his parents' funeral and said, "See, who says I can't fill my father's shoes. These are his shoes," she quotes him as saying.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 2</B> [<I><A HREF="nov02.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Lyle Menendez said that Mafia criminals were telling him to be careful about what he says and how he acts, according to Brian Andersen, Kitty Menendez's brother, who testified outside the presence of the jury about a conversation with Menendez a few months after the killings.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: November 1</B> [<I><A HREF="nov01.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Lyle Menendez's former fiancee testified that Menendez offered her money to lie on the stand and say Jose Menendez assaulted her.</P>

