<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles: Menendez</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/top-casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/top-casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>The Menendez Retrial: October 1995</H2>

<P>NOTE: These files are in a compressed format (zipped). You will need to <A HREF="/download/utility/">download an unzipping utility</A> to open them.</P>

<P>If you prefer, you may <A HREF="october.zip">download the entire month's transcripts</A> at once.</P>
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<H3>The Transcripts</H3>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: October 31</B> [<I><A HREF="oct31.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Lyle Menendez told a friend about tape recorded sessions with therapist Jerome Oziel where he talks about the murder of his parents, Glenn Stevens, a former friend of Menendez, testified.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: October 30</B> [<I><A HREF="oct30.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Under cross-examination, Amir Eslaminia, a former high school classmate of Erik Menendez, admitted that Lyle Menendez did not go through with the plot to have Eslaminia lie on the witness stand.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: October 27</B> [<I><A HREF="oct27.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Amir Eslaminia testified that Lyle Menendez sent him a letter asking him to lie on the witness stand.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: October 26</B> [<I><A HREF="oct26.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
A real estate broker, a jeep saleswoman and other witnesses testified about the Menendez brothers' lavish spending habits after their parents' death.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: October 25</B> [<I><A HREF="oct25.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Prosecutors announced that Dr. Irwin Golden, the coroner who performed the autopsies on Kitty and Jose Menendez, will not be called to testify.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: October 24</B> [<I><A HREF="oct24.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The Menendez brothers' former tennis coach testified that Erik Menendez hired him for $60,000 a year as a personal trainer.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: October 23</B> [<I><A HREF="oct23.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The prosecution continued to present evidence to support its theory that Lyle and Erik Menendez killed their parents for money and went on a wild spending spree after the murders. Mary Ellen Mahar, a jewelry saleswoman, testified that the brothers came to her store just four days after the murders and spent about $15,000 on three Rolex watches.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: October 20</B> [<I><A HREF="oct20.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The judge rejected a defense motion for a mistrial after attorney Leslie Abramson accused a prosecutor of improperly asking a witness whether Jose Menendez had complained that Erik Menendez had been "in  trouble."</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: October 19</B> [<I><A HREF="oct19.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Probate attorney Randy Wright testified that within 24 hours of the murders, Lyle and Erik Menendez sought his advice on where to find their parents' will.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: October 18</B> [<I><A HREF="oct18.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The wife of a probate attorney testified that the Menendez brothers frantically sought her husband's help in trying to find the family will. Prosecutors are trying to show that on the day after the murders the the brothers already were thinking about how to gain access to the family money.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: October 17</B> [<I><A HREF="oct17.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The prosecution called tennis coach Perry Berman to talk about his meeting with the Menendez brothers the night of the killings. Prosecutors maintain that the brothers intended the meeting as an alibi. Berman also testified that Jose Menendez was a strict parent who controlled many aspects of his sons' lives but showed them little affection.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: October 16</B> [<I><A HREF="oct16.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The jury listened to the audiotape of the 911 call Lyle Menendez made to police about 90 minutes after he and his brother killed their parents on August 20, 1989. On the tape, the brothers are heard screaming and crying, and at one point, Lyle said, "someone shot my mom and dad."</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: October 13</B> [<I><A HREF="oct13.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
The jury heard tapes of the brothers confessing to a therapist that they murdered their parents. "There was no way I was going to kill my parents without Erik's consent," Lyle, 27, told his former therapist Jerome Oziel. "I wanted (Erik) to sleep on it a couple of days."</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: October 12</B> [<I><A HREF="oct12.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
Completing opening statements, defense lawyer Charles Gessler said the Menendez brothers were driven out of fear to kill their parents after years of physical and sexual abuse.</P>

<P><B>Trial Transcript: October 11</B> [<I><A HREF="oct11.zip">Download Compressed File</A></I>]<BR>
In opening arguments, prosecutor David Conn said Erik and Lyle Menendez carefully calculated the shotgun killing of their parents in 1989 and they should be convicted of first degree murder regardless of the motive. Defense lawyer Leslie Abramson said the brothers were sexually abused and acted out of fear. She said they should be convicted of nothing more than manslaughter.</P>

<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
