<h2>Profile of the Jury (3/18/96)</h2>

Here's a profile of the current jury panel that deliberated the fate of Lyle and Erik Menendez. The jury had eight men and four women.<p>

<b>Juror 1:</b>  White male, 34 years old, married, employed as a postal worker. <p>

<b>Juror 2:</b>  White male, 64 years old, married with three children, retired electrical engineer. <p>

<b>Juror 3:</b>  White female, 63 years old, divorced, retired owner of a travel agency. <p>

<b>Juror 4:</b>  White male, 62 years old,  married with two children, retired school principal. <p>

<b>Juror 5:</b>  White male, 52 years old, married with three children, employed as a survey supervisor for a utility company. <p>

<b>Juror 6:</b>  Hispanic male, 43 years old, married with two children, employed as a postal clerk. <p>

<b>Juror 7:</b>  White male, 30 years old, single, employed as a truck driver and pilot. <p>

<b>Juror 8:</b>  White female, 36 years old, married with four children, employed as a post office secretary. <p>

<b>Juror 9:</b>  White female , 59 years old, married with four children, homemaker. <p>

<b>Juror 10:</b> White male, 37 years old, single, employed as a social security claims representative. <p>

<b>Juror 11:</b> White male, 25 years old, single, recent graduate of law school. <p>

<b>Juror 12:</b> Asian female, 42 years old, divorced with two children, employed as a real estate appraiser. <p>

