   allegations are and the reason they need this additional

   information, if it even exists, there are only six reports of

   positive residue, high-explosive residue in this entire case.

   If you discount nitroglycerin, which we've already told you

   we're not going to introduce at the scene because law

   enforcement carries ammunition and you can't really distinguish

   it.

            So in terms of this allegation that, you know,

   contamination in the laboratory or contamination at the crime

   scene, out of the hundreds of tests that were done, I believe

   there were 404 high-explosive tests done, only six showed

   positive results.  So there is not, contrary to what Mr. Jones

   is saying, evidence of this widespread contamination.

