   Inspector General's team got?

            MS. WILKINSON:  Yes.  What they do, your Honor, is

   they do a memorandum of interview, which is our 302.  They put

   the witness' name at the top, where the person is from, and

   they put their, you know, summary of the person's statement in

   most cases.

            THE COURT:  Sort of like a 302.

            MS. WILKINSON:  Yes.  And in some cases, the person is

   asked about five different cases:  Specifically do you know

   about this -- you know, relevant to UNABOM or Ok. Bomb.  And

   when we -- when the information is relevant to the Oklahoma

   City bombing or to the individual's general credibility, those



                                                                           203



   are disclosed.

