   discovery, that is.

            THE COURT:  All right.  Well, the exculpatory

   evidence -- most of that relates to things that we have to do

   in chambers, nonpublic.  We have the closed-circuit television

   issue for 9:00 in the morning.  I think rather than start up



                                                                           224



   anything else now, we'll just come back at 9:00 in the morning,

   considering the level of my patience here, so . . .

            MR. HARTZLER:  No objection.

            MS. WILKINSON:  Your Honor, we have two issues I

   believe we could resolve.  I believe they're questions

   Mr. Jones raised this morning.

            THE COURT:  Okay.

            MS. WILKINSON:  He asked about satellite photographs

   and we checked on the NASA 1A listing, and that is a

   photograph.  It says, "a shuttle photograph."  I don't know

   whether that means it's from the satellite, but it's available

   for the defense.  It's for McPherson, Kansas.  I have the

   picture with me.  It really doesn't show you anything; but

   we'll provide it, if Mr. Jones would like it.

            Mr. Jones, you can see how helpful that is.

            MR. JONES:  This is precisely what I was looking for,

   your Honor.

            MS. WILKINSON:  I think you can see Mr. McVeigh down

   there.

            MR. JONES:  And Mr. Hartzler and I count six agents --

            THE COURT:  What's the other one?

            MS. WILKINSON:  The polygraph information that

   Mr. Woods raised; and we are going to go back out to the field

   offices to collect -- to ensure that we have all the

   information, the questions, the charts and reports; and we



                                                                           225



   understand that in some cases, the polygraphers wrote a 302,

   not in all cases.  We will try and collect all of that

   information and provide it to both defendants.

            THE COURT:  All right.  We'll accept that offer.

            And we'll recess till 9:00 tomorrow morning.

       (Recess at 4:27 p.m.)

                            *  *  *  *  *

                       REPORTERS' CERTIFICATE

            We certify that the foregoing is a correct transcript

   from the record of proceedings in the above-entitled matter.

            Dated at Denver, Colorado, this 13th day of November,

   1996.



                                    ______________________________
