18   to sever these defendants at trial?



19   A.  That's correct.



20   Q.  Have you ever testified on the subject of joint trials and



21   the need for severance?



22   A.  No.



23   Q.  Have you ever published any articles on this subject?



24   A.  No.



25   Q.  Have you ever filed a severance motion?







                                            22



    Bryan Stevenson - Cross



1   A.  No.



2   Q.  In fact, one of the -- the case at least I associate you



3   most with is the McMillan case.



4   A.  Uh-huh.



5   Q.  You've testified about that case on a number of occasions.



6   A.  That's correct.



7   Q.  That was a case in which you were successful in



8   establishing, following the trial, that the defendant was in



9   fact innocent of the crime?



10   A.  That's correct.



