4   A.  Yeah, I do.



5   Q.  Okay.  And Judge Campbell testified that there is a problem



6   in a joint capital penalty phase of using mitigating evidence



7   against -- on behalf of one defendant as de facto aggravating



8   evidence against the other.  Is that your experience?



9   A.  Yes.  It happens even -- it happens even in single trials



10   where you're attempting to get an individualized determination.



11   The battle to keep mitigation from being aggravating and the



12   pains that are taken to make sure that the jury is clear that



13   that cannot be in a single trial is difficult.  In a



14   co-defendant trial, it's a racehorse.



15   Q.  Can you give us an example, using, for example, the --



