24   out the surveys?



25   A.  I think it took 15 to 20 minutes.  In that general area.







                                                                 141



                          Edward Bronson - Cross



 1   Q.  So basically, it would be the beginning part of class and



 2   then they would get into whatever the class subject matter was?



 3   A.  Typically, that was the situation.



 4   Q.  And did you give four versions of this survey to each of



 5   the classes?



 6   A.  Yes.



 7   Q.  One of the surveys being a composite survey or joint



 8   scenario of all three defendants?



 9   A.  Yes.  I would interleaf them to see that each class had a



10   fairly -- you wouldn't give one class like an engineering class



11   one version and then give a social science class another



12   version; so each of the classes got fairly equal division of



13   the various scenarios.



14   Q.  One out of every four students in a class would get the



15   joint scenario, for example?



16   A.  Yes.



