21   2, and 3, that there was a risk of what, the ditto effect,



22   would you call it?



23   A.  What I was referring to was the manner in which they would



24   report the reasons for their decision.



25   Q.  All right.







                                                                 180



                           Reid Hastie - Cross



 1   A.  I didn't -- I'm sure I didn't say that their decision was a



 2   ditto or a Xerox of another decision but that when they were



