24   judge's instructions to a jury to consider all of the factors



25   of the earlier identification and to make up their mind?  We







                                                                 184



                           Reid Hastie - Cross



 1   just decide as a matter that we're not going to even let the



 2   jurors hear about it.  Right?  That's what happens; right?



 3   A.  Yes, that's right.



 4   Q.  And as a social scientist, you think that's good, don't



 5   you?  That's the right thing for judges to do?



 6   A.  Boy, I don't think there is a simple answer in the general.



 7   If you want my opinion about whether it would improve the



 8   jurors' performance as a fact-finder in a specific case -- I'm



